01:07:07.563 --> 01:07:11.260
...Dr. Ludlow Branson
of Columbia University.

01:07:12.701 --> 01:07:14.566
Dr. Branson...

01:07:15.170 --> 01:07:18.628
...is a mathematician of some note.

01:07:18.807 --> 01:07:21.298
Yes. And he will now demonstrate...

01:07:21.476 --> 01:07:23.205
...that in fact...

01:07:23.378 --> 01:07:26.905
...Miss Russell's mammaries
are no more prominent...

01:07:27.082 --> 01:07:29.880
...than any of these other fine ladies'.

01:07:32.421 --> 01:07:33.683
Doctor.

01:07:35.190 --> 01:07:36.782
Doctor...

01:07:37.659 --> 01:07:39.923
...you forgot your calipers.

01:07:46.702 --> 01:07:49.933
Gentlemen, Mr. Hughes.

01:07:52.674 --> 01:07:55.199
Let us commence by calling this...

01:07:56.044 --> 01:07:58.342
...Mammary Exhibit Number One.

01:07:58.513 --> 01:08:04.281
Now, you'll see that the length
of the actual cleavage...

01:08:05.020 --> 01:08:08.217
...if I may, is...

01:08:09.257 --> 01:08:11.452
...5 inches and a quarter.

01:08:11.827 --> 01:08:13.192
Now if we move to Mammary Exhibit...

01:08:13.362 --> 01:08:14.829
<i>Dateline: Hollywoodland.</i>

01:08:14.997 --> 01:08:18.488
<i>Movie tycoon Howard Hughes</i>
<i>must have the greatest job in the land.</i>

01:08:18.667 --> 01:08:22.103
<i>Every night, the lucky guy escorts</i>
<i>a different beautiful woman...</i>

01:08:22.270 --> 01:08:24.203
<i>... to a different dazzling event.</i>

01:08:24.372 --> 01:08:29.037
<i>The TWA king always talks up</i>
<i>his airline as he escorts a succession...</i>

01:08:31.345 --> 01:08:33.473
<i>The Hercules, ladies and gentlemen.</i>

01:08:33.649 --> 01:08:35.116
<i>The Hercules.</i>

01:08:35.283 --> 01:08:39.219
<i>A plane, a boat, a flying city.</i>

01:08:39.388 --> 01:08:42.845
Don't forget, every bill comes to me.
They don't pay for anything.

01:08:43.024 --> 01:08:46.461
Those men decide whether to fund
the plane, so I need them happy.

01:08:46.828 --> 01:08:49.091
- You do what it takes.
- You betcha, boss.

01:08:49.497 --> 01:08:51.796
How are the girls
in the bomb department?

01:08:51.966 --> 01:08:55.801
Well, let's put it this way,
it'll be a regular boob buffet.

01:08:55.970 --> 01:08:59.064
I don't think the Air Corps men
will have trouble scoring.

01:08:59.241 --> 01:09:02.904
- Good.
<i>- And inside, 700 brave American soldiers...</i>

01:09:03.078 --> 01:09:07.572
<i>... a dozen Sherman tanks all winging</i>
<i>their way over the Atlantic...</i>

01:09:07.749 --> 01:09:10.183
<i>... free from the threats</i>
<i>of the U-boats below.</i>

01:09:10.352 --> 01:09:14.685
<i>Could Jules Verne himself have</i>
<i>ever imagined anything so magnificent?</i>

01:09:14.856 --> 01:09:18.792
<i>Could he have imagined her mammoth</i>
<i>wingspan, longer than a football field?</i>

01:09:19.060 --> 01:09:20.790
Don't you see how this demeans me?

01:09:20.962 --> 01:09:23.294
Since when do you care
about scandal rags?

01:09:23.465 --> 01:09:26.764
Every time there's a picture of you with
another woman, it's a slap in the face.

01:09:26.935 --> 01:09:29.904
- Don't you understand that?
- Well, that's overstating it.

01:09:30.072 --> 01:09:33.404
Joan Crawford, Ginger Rogers,
Linda Darnell, Joan Fontaine...

01:09:33.575 --> 01:09:36.475
...and now Bette Davis,
for God's sake.

01:09:38.345 --> 01:09:43.511
Look, they're Cracker Jack candy, honey.
They don't mean anything to me.

01:09:43.685 --> 01:09:46.654
Oh, very nice.

01:09:48.323 --> 01:09:51.224
You're the one that said
that all men are predators.

01:09:51.393 --> 01:09:54.294
I mean, it's all in Darwin, remember?

01:09:54.629 --> 01:09:58.224
And am I to expect this behavior
to continue after the wedding?

01:09:58.400 --> 01:10:00.459
What is really bothering you, Kate?

01:10:00.635 --> 01:10:03.900
Is it the women or the publicity?

01:10:09.144 --> 01:10:13.376
Can't you eat ice cream from a bowl
like everyone else in the world?

01:10:20.489 --> 01:10:24.050
Don't you dare.

01:10:35.737 --> 01:10:36.999
Yeah.

01:10:38.173 --> 01:10:41.768
No, Odie, this is not a good time.

01:10:42.010 --> 01:10:46.174
For chrissakes, we can't make The Hercules
if we don't have any aluminum.

01:10:46.348 --> 01:10:47.940
Wait.

01:10:48.116 --> 01:10:51.176
I can hear you better now.
Tell the War Production Board...

01:10:51.353 --> 01:10:54.550
...that this is an essential
strategic operation.

01:10:54.723 --> 01:10:59.285
If they're giving aluminum to Boeing,
they can give some to Hughes Aircraft.

01:10:59.461 --> 01:11:02.430
Don't set the ice cream...

01:11:02.597 --> 01:11:06.966
We gotta think of something else. If we
can't get aluminum, we'll find another way.

01:11:07.402 --> 01:11:10.735
You tell me. We'll find
some alloy that works just as well.

01:11:11.006 --> 01:11:13.634
Right. Look...

01:11:13.809 --> 01:11:17.939
- lf we can't get aluminum, we'll use wood.
- You can't make a plane out of wood.

01:11:18.113 --> 01:11:20.638
Why not?
The damn thing is a flying boat, right?

01:11:20.816 --> 01:11:22.784
- What do they use to make boats?
- Oak.

01:11:22.951 --> 01:11:25.886
And think of The Hercules
like a flying Spanish galleon.

01:11:26.054 --> 01:11:28.852
Spanish galleons
can weigh 1200 tons.

01:11:29.724 --> 01:11:31.555
Good luck today.

01:11:32.093 --> 01:11:35.426
We just have to find the right wood.
Something light but strong.

01:11:35.597 --> 01:11:38.395
- Morning, Kate.
- Pine, cedar, maybe birch.

01:11:48.910 --> 01:11:50.502
Catch.

01:11:54.416 --> 01:11:56.213
From my farm.

01:11:56.785 --> 01:11:59.379
If you like it, I can get you a bushel.

01:12:12.200 --> 01:12:14.634
Trouble with Mr. Hughes?

01:12:20.041 --> 01:12:24.478
There's too much Howard Hughes
in Howard Hughes.

01:12:26.314 --> 01:12:28.339
That's the trouble.

01:12:41.496 --> 01:12:43.293
Beautiful.

01:12:45.267 --> 01:12:46.666
Don't you take Christmas off?

01:12:48.003 --> 01:12:50.767
Nice to see you.
Sorry, I've got grease on my hands.

01:12:50.939 --> 01:12:53.464
Have we got something to show you.

01:12:57.846 --> 01:13:02.579
Take a look. The XF-11
reconnaissance flier. Spy plane, really.

01:13:03.518 --> 01:13:06.214
Designed every inch of her myself.

01:13:06.388 --> 01:13:08.379
She's got a top speed of 450...

01:13:08.556 --> 01:13:11.389
...which means she can outrun
anything they throw against her.

01:13:11.559 --> 01:13:14.653
After the Japs stole
my H-1 design for their Zeros...

01:13:14.829 --> 01:13:16.990
...I needed to do them one better.

01:13:18.099 --> 01:13:21.227
Yeah, she's my Buck Rogers ship.

01:13:21.403 --> 01:13:23.428
She's a looker.

01:13:24.072 --> 01:13:25.699
Okay, what do you got for me?

01:13:33.148 --> 01:13:35.378
Jiminy Cricket.

01:13:35.550 --> 01:13:39.213
Seating capacity for 60.
Wingspan, 123 feet.

01:13:39.387 --> 01:13:42.754
Four Double Cyclone engines.
Her ceiling's 25,000 feet.

01:13:42.924 --> 01:13:46.155
- Gross weight?
- 86,000, wing loading of 41 pounds.

01:13:46.328 --> 01:13:49.126
So less drag on the plane in thinner air.

01:13:49.297 --> 01:13:52.755
So high-cruise power, you're looking
at a top speed of around 340.

01:13:53.835 --> 01:13:57.396
Giving her a range of about 3000 miles.

01:13:58.573 --> 01:14:01.064
- Cross-country.
- Nonstop.

01:14:02.377 --> 01:14:03.935
Bob...

01:14:04.112 --> 01:14:07.275
...you know something?
You are a son of a bitch.

01:14:18.226 --> 01:14:21.718
Yeah. Bob, you got
something on your suit.

01:14:23.298 --> 01:14:24.765
Yeah.

01:14:25.133 --> 01:14:27.624
On your lapel.
You got something on your lapel.

01:14:30.772 --> 01:14:32.637
Right there, Bob.

01:14:34.409 --> 01:14:35.967
You missed it. Right there.

01:14:38.279 --> 01:14:40.144
Clean it off, would you?

01:14:40.315 --> 01:14:42.806
Here. Thanks.

01:14:46.087 --> 01:14:47.520
No, throw it away.

01:14:51.559 --> 01:14:52.958
No, over there.

01:14:59.467 --> 01:15:03.301
Thanks. So, what do you call her?

01:15:03.471 --> 01:15:05.632
The Constellation,
but we can change that.

01:15:05.807 --> 01:15:07.434
No, no.

01:15:07.609 --> 01:15:10.635
It's pretty. I like her.

01:15:11.613 --> 01:15:13.706
So, what kind of deal can you give me?

01:15:13.882 --> 01:15:15.679
What kind of deal can you give me?

01:15:15.850 --> 01:15:18.148
The first 40 planes off the assembly line.

01:15:18.319 --> 01:15:20.844
That should give us about
two years' exclusivity.

01:15:21.022 --> 01:15:22.319
Hell, more than that.

01:15:22.490 --> 01:15:26.483
United and American don't have
the imagination for a plane like this.

01:15:26.661 --> 01:15:29.255
Two years ahead of Juan Trippe, then.

01:15:34.302 --> 01:15:35.564
How much?

01:15:35.737 --> 01:15:37.898
Four hundred and fifty thousand each.

01:15:38.706 --> 01:15:41.573
So that's 18 million for the first 40.

01:15:42.510 --> 01:15:45.570
Hell, TWA can't afford that.
The damn airline's flat broke.

01:15:49.751 --> 01:15:52.219
Guess I'll just have
to pay for them myself.

01:15:53.121 --> 01:15:56.181
Build them, Bob.
Send the bill to Noah Dietrich.

01:15:56.357 --> 01:15:57.881
Oh, and thank you.

01:16:01.663 --> 01:16:03.494
Merry Christmas.

01:16:03.665 --> 01:16:08.125
<i>You've just placed the largest order for</i>
<i>airplanes in the history of the damn planet.</i>

01:16:08.303 --> 01:16:10.430
<i>Lockheed sent us a bill for $18 million.</i>

01:16:10.605 --> 01:16:13.870
Don't get all hysterical on me, Noah.
It isn't good for you.

01:16:14.042 --> 01:16:17.375
<i>- This is a lot of money for planes.</i>
- I know it's a lot of money.

01:16:17.545 --> 01:16:21.174
<i>It's too damn much. You think I've got</i>
<i>$18 million in petty cash?</i>

01:16:21.349 --> 01:16:23.510
I should've told you. It slipped my mind.

01:16:23.685 --> 01:16:25.585
<i>- Slipped your mind? Oh, for...</i>
- Right.

01:16:25.753 --> 01:16:29.211
- I'll get back to you. Bye.
<i>- How could $18 million slip your mind?</i>

01:16:30.091 --> 01:16:33.254
Hey, honey.
What are you doing home?

01:16:37.699 --> 01:16:40.532
You're not one for tears, and, well...

01:16:40.702 --> 01:16:44.968
...neither am I,
so it's best to come out with it.

01:16:48.076 --> 01:16:52.308
I've met someone.
I've fallen in love and I'm moving out.

01:16:54.916 --> 01:16:59.683
If I could make it
any more gentle, I would.

01:16:59.854 --> 01:17:03.915
But I can't, so...

01:17:04.959 --> 01:17:06.859
...there we both are.

01:17:10.465 --> 01:17:12.296
Let's be honest.

01:17:12.467 --> 01:17:16.961
It's all been a grand adventure,
but it couldn't possibly last.

01:17:17.138 --> 01:17:20.039
We're too alike, you and I.

01:17:23.178 --> 01:17:24.475
You met someone?

01:17:24.646 --> 01:17:28.582
Someone more appropriate.
To me, I mean.

01:17:31.286 --> 01:17:34.255
What does that mean,
"more appropriate"?

01:17:34.656 --> 01:17:38.752
Someone more attuned to my needs.

01:17:39.294 --> 01:17:41.228
Look at me, Katie.

01:17:41.396 --> 01:17:43.296
Stop acting.

01:17:43.731 --> 01:17:46.529
I'm not acting.

01:17:51.139 --> 01:17:53.767
I wonder if you even know anymore.

01:17:58.680 --> 01:18:00.910
Don't be unkind.

01:18:03.618 --> 01:18:05.313
You?

01:18:06.654 --> 01:18:07.985
You wanna go?

01:18:11.626 --> 01:18:13.253
Go on.

01:18:13.828 --> 01:18:16.956
Actresses are cheap in this town, darling.

01:18:17.131 --> 01:18:19.725
- And I got a lot of money.
- This is beneath you.

01:18:19.901 --> 01:18:22.335
No, no, this is exactly me.

01:18:22.503 --> 01:18:27.634
You tell me you're leaving me, and you
have the nerve to expect graciousness?

01:18:28.109 --> 01:18:30.100
I expect a little maturity.

01:18:30.278 --> 01:18:33.179
I expect you to face the situation
like an adult who...

01:18:33.348 --> 01:18:35.646
Don't talk down to me!

01:18:35.817 --> 01:18:38.809
Don't you ever talk down to me!
You are a movie star.

01:18:38.987 --> 01:18:40.545
Nothing more.

01:19:52.593 --> 01:19:54.527
<i>Don't answer it.</i>

01:19:57.398 --> 01:19:59.093
What is it, Howard?

01:19:59.267 --> 01:20:01.565
<i>Hey, Noah...</i>

01:20:01.736 --> 01:20:04.728
...I need you to get to Penney's
and buy me some clothes.

01:20:04.906 --> 01:20:06.703
- Penney's isn't open.
- Oh, shit.

01:20:06.874 --> 01:20:09.809
- It's 2 in the morning.
- Yeah, that's right.

01:20:09.977 --> 01:20:12.707
Well, first thing tomorrow, then, all right?

01:20:12.880 --> 01:20:15.940
I need two new suits off the rack.
One light and one dark.

01:20:16.117 --> 01:20:19.348
Three white shirts and three pairs
of white tennis shoes. Got that?

01:20:19.520 --> 01:20:21.454
- Yeah.
- No, no.

01:20:21.622 --> 01:20:23.453
- Make it Woolworth's.
- Woolworth's.

01:20:23.624 --> 01:20:26.218
No, no, Penney's. Penney's.

01:20:26.394 --> 01:20:28.123
All right.

01:20:28.830 --> 01:20:31.628
I'll get into it as soon as I can, Howard.

01:20:31.966 --> 01:20:34.526
- All right?
- Noah, do you have a recorder?

01:20:35.236 --> 01:20:38.433
- No.
- Are you recording this conversation?

01:20:38.606 --> 01:20:41.006
- No.
- Okay.

01:20:41.175 --> 01:20:43.006
I trust you.

01:20:44.045 --> 01:20:47.412
- Howard...
- I need those suits first thing tomorrow.

01:20:47.582 --> 01:20:51.040
- All right.
- Wait. Did I say Penney's or Woolworth's?

01:20:51.219 --> 01:20:53.847
- Penney's.
- Better make it Sears.

01:20:54.021 --> 01:20:56.512
All right, then, Sears.

01:20:59.394 --> 01:21:01.555
I'm sorry, honey.

01:21:02.764 --> 01:21:05.028
If I don't answer, he'll just call back.

01:21:26.921 --> 01:21:29.947
Stop there, if you please, Miss Domergue.

01:21:35.830 --> 01:21:37.730
Have you had surgery, Miss Domergue?

01:21:39.600 --> 01:21:41.067
No.

01:21:41.903 --> 01:21:44.997
Do you have scars of any kind?

01:21:46.407 --> 01:21:47.931
No.

01:21:49.577 --> 01:21:51.704
Wipe off your lipstick.

01:21:56.284 --> 01:21:57.546
That's much better.

01:21:59.153 --> 01:22:04.056
Now, you understand that you'd be
under contract to me? Personally.

01:22:04.992 --> 01:22:07.119
Do you know what that means?

01:22:15.470 --> 01:22:17.233
Now turn around for me.

01:22:25.513 --> 01:22:27.003
Very nice.

01:22:28.149 --> 01:22:30.014
You move well.

01:22:32.854 --> 01:22:34.822
You live with your family, do you?

01:22:36.924 --> 01:22:38.516
Yes.

01:22:38.993 --> 01:22:40.517
That's nice.

01:22:41.863 --> 01:22:43.626
Tell me something.

01:22:44.999 --> 01:22:47.399
How old are you, Miss Domergue?

01:22:50.371 --> 01:22:52.134
Fifteen.

01:22:55.543 --> 01:22:56.703
Holy Mother of God.

01:23:16.129 --> 01:23:19.929
Well, a car picks me up
every morning at 8, and off I go.

01:23:20.099 --> 01:23:23.125
I'm getting my high school diploma.

01:23:23.303 --> 01:23:25.999
Howard thinks that education is important.

01:23:26.172 --> 01:23:28.572
- That's right.
- And then, after classes...

01:23:28.741 --> 01:23:32.302
...I'm off for elocution
and grooming and fittings.

01:23:32.478 --> 01:23:34.275
Well, blow me down.

01:23:35.481 --> 01:23:37.711
Pan Am's working
out of the Cocoanut Grove?

01:23:37.884 --> 01:23:39.818
- Hello, Jack.
- Hello, Juan.

01:23:39.986 --> 01:23:41.715
Helen, good to see you.

01:23:41.888 --> 01:23:44.379
- How are you, Howard?
- Good, thanks.

01:23:44.557 --> 01:23:46.354
- This is Faith Domergue.
- Sit down.

01:23:46.526 --> 01:23:48.391
- Pleasure.
- What are you doing here?

01:23:48.561 --> 01:23:51.359
Well, I'm out to meet
with Douglas about the DC-4.

01:23:51.531 --> 01:23:55.399
It's our new plane, and it is
gonna be a pip, let me tell you.

01:23:55.568 --> 01:23:58.765
- How's the Constellation coming?
- Good.

01:23:59.072 --> 01:24:00.334
Great.

01:24:01.741 --> 01:24:04.232
So how about letting me steal a peek?

01:24:06.212 --> 01:24:08.180
I don't think so.

01:24:08.348 --> 01:24:11.374
I should be cross with you.
You stole Ray Loewy from us.

01:24:12.185 --> 01:24:15.712
- He's doing our interior design. That's right.
- He was doing ours.

01:24:18.224 --> 01:24:19.987
So...

01:24:20.526 --> 01:24:22.994
...what are your colors?
- Stop fishing.

01:24:24.731 --> 01:24:27.222
So you have buttons...

01:24:27.400 --> 01:24:28.833
...or zippers?

01:24:29.268 --> 01:24:30.530
I'm sorry?

01:24:32.472 --> 01:24:36.374
Buttons or zippers for the drapes
on the sleeping berths?

01:24:39.879 --> 01:24:41.540
Zippers.

01:24:50.456 --> 01:24:52.014
Buttons.

01:25:01.701 --> 01:25:04.693
So I suppose you'll be
expanding on down to Mexico.

01:25:05.204 --> 01:25:08.731
- Why do you say that?
- Well, your range is 3000 miles.

01:25:08.908 --> 01:25:13.004
I'd imagine you'd expand from Los Angeles
to Mexico and South America.

01:25:13.179 --> 01:25:15.340
Hey, that's a good idea.
Anyone got a pen?

01:25:15.515 --> 01:25:17.642
Or across the Atlantic.

01:25:20.653 --> 01:25:22.553
You've had enough of this ice cream.

01:25:22.722 --> 01:25:26.283
You give me that spoon. You don't
wanna get your gloves all sticky.

01:25:28.261 --> 01:25:30.126
Isn't that too far?

01:25:35.168 --> 01:25:37.068
New York...

01:25:37.236 --> 01:25:39.261
...to Newfoundland...

01:25:39.972 --> 01:25:41.234
...to Ireland.

01:25:46.479 --> 01:25:48.071
To Paris.

01:25:55.221 --> 01:25:56.848
Well...

01:25:57.390 --> 01:25:59.483
...Pan Am welcomes you.

01:25:59.659 --> 01:26:01.490
We're overbooked as it is.

01:26:01.661 --> 01:26:05.290
It's such a burden doing it all
on your own, let me tell you.

01:26:05.465 --> 01:26:07.524
So when's the Connie gonna be ready?

01:26:07.700 --> 01:26:10.328
- Next year maybe. DC-4?
- Next year.

01:26:10.503 --> 01:26:13.666
Well, we look forward to her then.

01:26:14.240 --> 01:26:15.969
And I to the Connie.

01:26:17.844 --> 01:26:21.473
I've ordered the next 40 after you.

01:26:21.714 --> 01:26:23.477
- It's Miss?
- Domergue.

01:26:23.649 --> 01:26:27.016
Yes, of course. Now, was that a
rumba or a samba you were doing?

01:26:27.453 --> 01:26:30.183
- It was a samba.
- A samba, yes.

01:26:30.356 --> 01:26:33.621
Howard, I never knew
you were such a good dancer.

01:26:34.594 --> 01:26:36.425
Helen, Jack.

01:26:38.264 --> 01:26:41.062
Good going. You gave away
our entire postwar strategy.

01:26:41.234 --> 01:26:45.694
- He can't stop us.
- He's Pan Am. He can stop anything.

01:26:47.740 --> 01:26:49.537
Give me the largest
Scotch you got.

01:26:49.709 --> 01:26:53.304
I don't know what in the hell you're
so damn giddy about. Excuse me.

01:28:45.391 --> 01:28:46.824
Jack.

01:28:46.993 --> 01:28:50.622
Get in touch with Joyce and Berg.
Those are my boys in Washington.

01:28:50.796 --> 01:28:54.197
Set up a meeting with Jones,
secretary of commerce, old golfing buddy.

01:28:54.367 --> 01:28:57.302
- Slow down.
- We'll need terminals in Ireland and France.

01:28:57.470 --> 01:28:58.937
I wanna get some tax breaks.

01:28:59.105 --> 01:29:02.768
If that ass thinks he owns the world,
he's got another thing coming.

01:29:02.942 --> 01:29:05.809
Pan Am owns Europe.
We ought to think about Mexico.

01:29:05.978 --> 01:29:10.074
To hell with Mexico. No airline should
have a monopoly on flying the Atlantic.

01:29:10.249 --> 01:29:13.548
It just isn't fair.
He owns Pan Am, he owns Congress.

01:29:13.719 --> 01:29:17.553
He owns the Civil Aeronautics Board,
but he does not own the sky.

01:29:17.723 --> 01:29:20.351
We're in a street fight
with that son of a bitch.

01:29:20.526 --> 01:29:24.189
I've been fighting high-hat
Ivy League pricks like him my whole life.

01:29:24.363 --> 01:29:27.992
And listen, fire Ray Loewy.
You goddamn heard me? Fire Ray Loewy.

01:29:28.167 --> 01:29:31.568
He's spying for Trippe.
That shitheel knew all about the buttons.

01:29:31.737 --> 01:29:33.705
Spies in my midst, Jack.

01:29:34.407 --> 01:29:36.204
Spies in my midst.

01:29:50.656 --> 01:29:53.557
- Hello, Howard.
- Roland.

01:29:55.461 --> 01:29:57.019
So...

01:29:57.196 --> 01:29:58.720
...what can I do for you?

01:30:01.934 --> 01:30:05.927
I want all the pictures you have
of Kate Hepburn and Spencer Tracy.

01:30:06.105 --> 01:30:09.632
All the negatives.
And I want you to kill the story.

01:30:09.809 --> 01:30:13.176
Howard, he's a married man.
He's a Catholic.

01:30:13.346 --> 01:30:15.610
They're movie stars.
Fair game all around.

01:30:24.090 --> 01:30:26.251
My office knows where I am, Howard.

01:30:27.293 --> 01:30:30.091
I'm not gonna kill you, Roland.

01:30:30.262 --> 01:30:32.196
I don't do that.

01:30:36.936 --> 01:30:39.564
- How much?
- Not for sale.

01:30:42.842 --> 01:30:44.400
How much?

01:30:45.277 --> 01:30:48.440
Not for sale.

01:30:51.784 --> 01:30:53.877
You ever cheat on your wife, Roland?

01:30:55.688 --> 01:30:58.122
You ever screw a colored girl?

01:30:58.824 --> 01:31:01.987
You ever steal anything?
You ever hurt anyone?

01:31:04.130 --> 01:31:05.961
Good night, Howard.

01:31:06.365 --> 01:31:09.334
You ever go to
a Communist Party meeting, Roland?

01:31:19.178 --> 01:31:21.305
TWA stock.

01:31:22.348 --> 01:31:23.610
How much?

01:31:25.217 --> 01:31:26.684
Fifty thousand shares.

01:31:27.319 --> 01:31:28.786
Ten.

01:31:31.857 --> 01:31:33.188
All right.

01:31:36.295 --> 01:31:38.126
This isn't gonna be that easy.

01:31:38.497 --> 01:31:41.898
He's been making big contributions
on both sides of the aisle.

01:31:42.068 --> 01:31:45.504
And Jack Frye is out there
lobbying everybody in town.

01:31:45.671 --> 01:31:48.834
The French and British ambassadors
are lined up on his side.

01:31:50.176 --> 01:31:53.339
I'm telling you, TWA is serious
about going international.

01:31:53.512 --> 01:31:55.139
Okay.

01:31:55.314 --> 01:31:57.248
Point, Mr. Hughes.

01:31:57.616 --> 01:32:01.279
I think it's time for you to introduce
the community airline bill...

01:32:01.454 --> 01:32:02.978
...on the floor of the Senate.

01:32:03.989 --> 01:32:06.787
- Is it done?
- My people are finishing it right now.

01:32:06.959 --> 01:32:11.487
I also have to get you on the committee
investigating the national defense.

01:32:13.933 --> 01:32:16.993
On the committee or chairman?

01:32:17.336 --> 01:32:19.998
I could be much more effective
as chairman.

01:32:20.172 --> 01:32:23.938
It's a great public platform.
You know, it generates a lot of press.

01:32:24.110 --> 01:32:27.568
- Wasn't Truman chairman of that committee?
- Yeah, right.

01:32:27.746 --> 01:32:30.146
He's vice president.
Look what he did with it.

01:32:30.316 --> 01:32:32.375
No, I think...

01:32:33.085 --> 01:32:35.019
I think chairman.

01:32:35.688 --> 01:32:37.121
What do you think?

01:32:39.158 --> 01:32:41.718
- Chairman. That is interesting.
- Yeah.

01:32:41.894 --> 01:32:45.386
Let me show you
these specs for the DC-4.

01:32:45.664 --> 01:32:49.122
Ava, what do you think about
Trans World Airlines?

01:32:49.301 --> 01:32:51.826
Transcontinental and Western
doesn't fit anymore.

01:32:52.004 --> 01:32:54.871
We're international,
we need a name that reflects that.

01:32:55.040 --> 01:32:57.736
Trans World is good. Kind of peppy.

01:32:57.910 --> 01:33:00.435
TWA, right?

01:33:00.613 --> 01:33:03.377
That way you don't need
to repaint any of the planes.

01:33:03.549 --> 01:33:05.710
That's you. Always pinching pennies.

01:33:06.886 --> 01:33:08.877
Hand me my wrap.

01:33:22.902 --> 01:33:25.063
Knock it off.

01:33:31.277 --> 01:33:33.802
I have something for you.

01:33:35.047 --> 01:33:36.878
Stay here.

01:33:42.354 --> 01:33:45.016
- What the hell is this?
- It's a present.

01:33:45.191 --> 01:33:47.091
Go on, open it.

01:33:48.260 --> 01:33:51.718
Oh, a box of trash.
You shouldn't have.

01:33:51.897 --> 01:33:53.592
Keep looking, keep looking.

01:33:58.437 --> 01:34:00.496
It's a Kashmiri sapphire.

01:34:00.673 --> 01:34:03.801
I had my boys all over
the damn globe looking for this.

01:34:03.976 --> 01:34:05.238
Why?

01:34:05.411 --> 01:34:06.673
Because.

01:34:06.845 --> 01:34:08.472
Look.

01:34:08.647 --> 01:34:10.706
It matches your eyes.

01:34:10.883 --> 01:34:13.249
I am not for sale.

01:34:13.419 --> 01:34:15.478
For chrissakes, it's just a present.

01:34:15.654 --> 01:34:18.851
You can't buy me, Howard,
so stop trying.

01:34:19.024 --> 01:34:22.585
Don't buy me any more diamonds
or sapphires or any other damn thing.

01:34:22.761 --> 01:34:25.195
You can buy me dinner.
How about that?

01:34:25.931 --> 01:34:27.193
Jesus, Ava.

01:34:28.234 --> 01:34:31.294
It's bad enough I have to endure
those gym shoes of yours.

01:34:31.470 --> 01:34:35.133
But I get all dolled up and we go out
in this jalopy without a hood.

01:34:36.575 --> 01:34:39.703
Ava, will you marry me?

01:34:39.878 --> 01:34:42.574
- No, Howard.
- Well, why not, for heaven's sake?

01:34:42.748 --> 01:34:45.308
In the first place, I don't love you.

01:34:45.484 --> 01:34:47.850
In the second place, I'm still married.

01:34:48.020 --> 01:34:52.719
Look, you got girls stashed all over town.
You got a damn harem just at the Bel-Air.

01:34:52.891 --> 01:34:54.825
Marry one of your bungalow girls.

01:34:54.994 --> 01:34:58.794
Those are employees. I won't marry
an employee. How would that look?

01:35:06.972 --> 01:35:08.234
What is going on?

01:35:11.543 --> 01:35:14.171
- Oh, my God!
- Goddamn it!

01:35:15.814 --> 01:35:17.076
Faith!

01:35:17.850 --> 01:35:19.784
- Faith, what the hell?
- Look out!

01:35:19.952 --> 01:35:22.648
Goddamn, what the hell are you doing?

01:35:25.824 --> 01:35:28.588
- Are you okay, lady?
- What are you doing with her?

01:35:28.761 --> 01:35:31.423
We are going to dinner.
Now, get out of there.

01:35:31.597 --> 01:35:33.588
Get that crazy bitch away from me!

01:35:33.766 --> 01:35:35.358
Don't you love me anymore?

01:35:35.534 --> 01:35:37.092
Course I love you, pork chop.

01:35:37.269 --> 01:35:39.032
Ava, look over here. Howard.

01:35:39.772 --> 01:35:41.034
Hey.

01:35:44.476 --> 01:35:47.104
<i>Juan Trippe is working</i>
<i>with Senator Brewster now.</i>

01:35:47.279 --> 01:35:51.613
They're after you. If the community
airline bill becomes law, we are finished.

01:35:51.784 --> 01:35:53.877
Pan Am will have a monopoly
on international travel.

01:35:54.053 --> 01:35:56.578
Well, how can they justify it?
It's un-American.

01:35:56.755 --> 01:36:00.589
Brewster is saying that nationalized
foreign carriers, like Air France...

01:36:00.759 --> 01:36:03.785
...can offer lower rates because
they don't have to compete.

01:36:03.962 --> 01:36:07.261
Let's get rid of competition
and have a nationalized airline...

01:36:07.433 --> 01:36:10.493
...and why don't we make it Pan Am?
- I'm not kowtowing to anyone.

01:36:10.669 --> 01:36:12.933
- Howard, I need you up here.
- One sec, Odie.

01:36:13.105 --> 01:36:15.630
Look, we are Trans World Airlines,
all right?

01:36:15.808 --> 01:36:20.177
Get me something with a circle or a globe
or something round, for God's sake.

01:36:20.346 --> 01:36:21.608
- Speak up.
- One cut.

01:36:21.780 --> 01:36:25.944
I don't give a rat's ass. I'm not making
a cut. I'll release it without a seal.

01:36:26.118 --> 01:36:27.813
We gotta go public with this.

01:36:27.986 --> 01:36:29.851
I'm gonna talk to Hearst...

01:36:30.022 --> 01:36:33.185
...but we gotta get
some senators on our side.

01:36:33.359 --> 01:36:35.759
- What do you want me to do?
- What Trippe does.

01:36:35.928 --> 01:36:38.658
Offshore operations.
See who's up for re-election...

01:36:38.831 --> 01:36:41.425
...let's start making donations.
- Bribe senators?

01:36:41.867 --> 01:36:44.529
I don't want them bribed.
I want it done legally.

01:36:44.703 --> 01:36:48.036
I want them bought.
Put a team of investigators on Brewster.

01:36:48.207 --> 01:36:50.539
I need to know everything
about that shitbag.

01:36:50.709 --> 01:36:53.610
Where he goes, what he says
and who he screws.

01:36:53.779 --> 01:36:55.770
- Get into it right now.
- You got it.

01:37:03.422 --> 01:37:04.855
Just give me a second.

01:37:07.192 --> 01:37:10.184
- All right, what do you need?
- Rudder and elevators.

01:37:10.863 --> 01:37:12.922
No. These are fine.

01:37:13.098 --> 01:37:17.194
Have Simon and Pete get back to me on the
assemblies. We need a secondary system.

01:37:17.369 --> 01:37:18.859
Okay.

01:37:19.671 --> 01:37:22.367
Listen, we need to take
another look at the wheel.

01:37:22.541 --> 01:37:25.339
- Jesus. The damn wheel?
- Yeah.

01:37:25.511 --> 01:37:27.035
It just doesn't feel right.

01:37:27.212 --> 01:37:31.205
Christ almighty, you've seen 8000
goddamn wheels. Choose one, please.

01:37:31.383 --> 01:37:33.180
- Just one of them.
- I know, I know.

01:37:33.352 --> 01:37:35.718
- This one?
- I know, this one...

01:37:35.888 --> 01:37:39.722
This one's pretty close. Pretty close.

01:38:15.761 --> 01:38:17.251
Odie.

01:38:18.163 --> 01:38:20.688
That man sweeping up over there...

01:38:20.866 --> 01:38:23.926
...does he work for me?
I mean, have you seen him before?

01:38:24.102 --> 01:38:26.662
Name's Nick, something like that.

01:38:28.907 --> 01:38:30.670
Why's he looking at me?

01:38:32.878 --> 01:38:34.311
I don't know.

01:38:36.415 --> 01:38:39.543
Fire him. And make sure
they use damp brooms from now on.

01:38:39.718 --> 01:38:43.085
Respiratory diseases are expensive,
and I don't want lawsuits.

01:38:43.255 --> 01:38:46.156
But can we at least proceed
with the instrument panel?

01:38:46.325 --> 01:38:48.759
- The tool shop's ready.
- I wanna see the blueprints.

01:38:48.927 --> 01:38:51.896
Look, Howard, the deadline
is now completely unrealistic.

01:38:52.064 --> 01:38:54.589
The war is gonna be over
by the time she's done.

01:38:54.766 --> 01:38:58.964
I need you to help consult on vital decisions,
and you're off dealing with movies.

01:38:59.137 --> 01:39:02.106
You got 1000 workers waiting
for you to make a decision...

01:39:02.274 --> 01:39:03.901
Hey, Odie!

01:39:04.076 --> 01:39:06.067
Take it easy, all right.

01:39:06.245 --> 01:39:10.272
You're under pressure, but it's gonna
do me no good if you crack up on me.

01:39:10.983 --> 01:39:12.712
All right? Look...

01:39:12.885 --> 01:39:15.217
...take a couple of hours off, all right.

01:39:15.387 --> 01:39:17.252
- You just relax a little.
- Okay.

01:39:17.689 --> 01:39:19.714
- See your wife.
- Okay.

01:39:20.125 --> 01:39:21.490
All right.

01:39:22.361 --> 01:39:25.592
- Be sure to show me all the blueprints.
- All right.

01:39:27.232 --> 01:39:29.462
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:29.935 --> 01:39:31.926
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:32.104 --> 01:39:35.733
I'm serious, now.
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:37.342 --> 01:39:38.969
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:39.144 --> 01:39:42.045
- Howard.
- Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:42.214 --> 01:39:44.148
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:44.316 --> 01:39:45.874
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:46.051 --> 01:39:48.110
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:48.287 --> 01:39:50.380
I wanna get this done right.

01:39:51.156 --> 01:39:52.589
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:52.758 --> 01:39:54.487
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:54.660 --> 01:39:57.254
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:57.429 --> 01:39:58.987
Show me all the blueprints.

01:39:59.164 --> 01:40:01.098
- Howard.
- Show me all the blueprints.

01:40:01.266 --> 01:40:04.929
Show me all the blueprints.
Show me all the blueprints...

01:40:31.930 --> 01:40:34.364
Quarantine.

01:40:35.400 --> 01:40:37.095
Q...

01:40:37.269 --> 01:40:39.237
...U...

01:40:39.404 --> 01:40:41.634
...A...

01:40:42.274 --> 01:40:44.242
...R...

01:40:44.910 --> 01:40:46.844
...A...

