...N...

01:40:59.458 --> 01:41:01.483
...E.

01:41:04.396 --> 01:41:06.489
Quarantine.

01:41:44.503 --> 01:41:47.563
General McEwan. Colonel Bertrang.
Thanks for coming down.

01:41:47.739 --> 01:41:49.900
Odie, you reading me okay?

01:41:50.075 --> 01:41:51.303
Yeah, you're A-okay.

01:41:56.948 --> 01:42:00.145
<i>All right, flight controls are active.</i>
<i>She's all yours.</i>

01:42:09.061 --> 01:42:11.393
Spotless.
No wiggle on the wheel or throttle.

01:42:11.563 --> 01:42:13.394
<i>Take it easy.</i>

01:42:30.415 --> 01:42:34.010
- How does she sound, Howard?
- She's whispering to me, buddy.

01:42:34.186 --> 01:42:36.086
All right, make her sing.

01:42:56.975 --> 01:43:00.206
Well, Odie, she can fly. Congratulations.

01:43:00.378 --> 01:43:03.870
I'm glad to hear it. Retract landing gear
and climb to 5000 feet...

01:43:04.049 --> 01:43:05.607
...on a heading of 2-7-0.

01:43:05.784 --> 01:43:11.654
Retracting landing gear and climbing
to 5000 feet on a heading 2-7-0.

01:43:16.161 --> 01:43:18.356
- She's fast.
- What's your air speed?

01:43:18.530 --> 01:43:20.157
292.

01:43:20.365 --> 01:43:23.892
<i>- All right, take her back to 200.</i>
- No damn way.

01:43:49.694 --> 01:43:51.423
We gotta bring her home.

01:43:51.596 --> 01:43:54.030
<i>Scheduled time of one hour</i>
<i>and 45 minutes has elapsed.</i>

01:43:54.232 --> 01:43:57.167
<i>- Set course for 0-9-0...</i>
- Ten more minutes. Roger that.

01:43:57.335 --> 01:43:59.929
<i>Negative, Howard. Bring her home.</i>

01:44:00.105 --> 01:44:05.975
Okay. Okay. Setting course for 0-9-0.

01:44:06.678 --> 01:44:08.578
Preparing to descend.

01:44:12.217 --> 01:44:15.482
- Jesus.
<i>- What is it, Howard?</i>

01:44:16.788 --> 01:44:20.280
The right wing just dipped.
I'm losing starboard engine.

01:44:20.725 --> 01:44:23.353
Increasing power to 2800 rpm.

01:44:23.829 --> 01:44:25.057
Cutting back.

01:44:25.430 --> 01:44:27.364
Increasing starboard engine only.

01:44:28.500 --> 01:44:31.230
Cutting back. I'm losing altitude.

01:44:31.403 --> 01:44:33.963
Check starboard-engine manifold pressure.

01:44:34.840 --> 01:44:38.708
- It's good, but rpm's are low.
<i>- Are both starboard props turning?</i>

01:44:38.877 --> 01:44:40.344
Hold on.

01:44:40.579 --> 01:44:43.605
They are, but she's pulling me
back and starboard, Odie.

01:44:43.782 --> 01:44:46.376
- How bad is your cross control?
- I'm at full left rudder...

01:44:46.551 --> 01:44:49.850
...and full left aileron,
but she won't stay level. Goddamn it.

01:44:50.121 --> 01:44:52.988
- Give us your position.
- Two thousand feet over...

01:44:53.158 --> 01:44:57.219
Oh, Christ, I don't know, Beverly Hills.
Fifteen hundred feet.

01:44:57.395 --> 01:44:59.090
We're going down.

01:45:00.031 --> 01:45:03.626
I'll try for the Wilshire Country Club.
Ninth hole. You reading me?

01:45:03.802 --> 01:45:07.738
<i>Wilshire Country Club, copy that.</i>
<i>Howard, reduce engines to 1000.</i>

01:45:08.440 --> 01:45:13.400
I'm going down!
I'm not gonna make it, buddy!

01:45:19.885 --> 01:45:21.682
Goddamn it!

01:47:24.042 --> 01:47:27.534
Is there anyone else inside?
Is there anyone else?!

01:47:27.712 --> 01:47:29.407
No.

01:47:33.251 --> 01:47:36.618
I'm Howard Hughes, the aviator.

01:47:45.897 --> 01:47:48.593
- every inch of his
wiring and fluid connection.

01:47:48.767 --> 01:47:51.429
He has burns to 78 percent of his body.

01:47:51.603 --> 01:47:54.265
Nine ribs are shattered,
not broken, shattered...

01:47:54.773 --> 01:47:59.233
...as are his nose, his chin, his cheek,
his left knee, his left elbow.

01:47:59.411 --> 01:48:02.005
He has 60 lacerations
on his face, to the bone.

01:48:02.580 --> 01:48:05.344
His chest was crushed,
so his left lung collapsed...

01:48:05.517 --> 01:48:09.180
...and his heart has shifted
to the right side of his chest cavity.

01:48:10.121 --> 01:48:12.021
Jesus, God.

01:48:12.457 --> 01:48:16.791
- He's getting blood transfusions now, but...
- Whose blood?

01:48:17.629 --> 01:48:19.790
- I'm sorry?
- Whose blood?

01:48:20.298 --> 01:48:21.856
From our stock.

01:48:22.534 --> 01:48:26.698
- Oh, he's not going to like that.
- Mr. Dietrich, I doubt he's...

01:48:26.871 --> 01:48:29.806
...ever gonna like or
dislike anything again.

01:48:30.442 --> 01:48:32.603
I'm terribly sorry.

01:49:01.072 --> 01:49:02.972
<i>Orange juice.</i>

01:49:06.077 --> 01:49:09.513
It's not fresh from the kitchen, so I...

01:49:10.215 --> 01:49:15.312
I have them make it here so...
So I can see.

01:49:19.424 --> 01:49:21.358
Look at me.

01:49:23.995 --> 01:49:25.986
I'm a monster.

01:49:26.464 --> 01:49:31.265
Yeah. Orange juice has nutritional value.

01:49:32.437 --> 01:49:37.397
There's... There's some flies
outside my window, though.

01:49:37.976 --> 01:49:39.739
So...

01:49:41.779 --> 01:49:44.441
...little Howard likes...

01:49:45.917 --> 01:49:48.044
...citrus.

01:49:48.820 --> 01:49:50.685
Don't he just?

01:49:53.825 --> 01:49:55.520
Tell me.

01:49:57.162 --> 01:50:00.962
An oil seal ripped off
the starboard rear propeller.

01:50:01.132 --> 01:50:04.590
When the pressure dropped,
the prop reversed pitch.

01:50:05.103 --> 01:50:06.866
Do you understand me?

01:50:07.405 --> 01:50:12.399
Howard, I'm sorry to have to tell you
this now, but there's something else.

